). These all originated as names for different parts of a single estate, appearing simply as <i>Devrel</i> in the <i>Domesday Book</i>. The river is thought to be named from Welsh <i>dwfr</i> ‘river’ + <i>iâl</i> ‘fertile uplands’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":15,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Deverell was born in 1244, in Pershore, Worcestershire, England. He had at least 1 son. He died about 1274, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1244–about 1274":"1244–umbes 1274","1258–1320":"1258–1320","1244–1274":"1244–1274","1259":"1259","1258":"1258","1244":"1244","1320":"1320","1274":"1274","about 1274":"umbes 1274","Pershore, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, England","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1244–about 1274":"1244–noin 1274","1258–1320":"1258–1320","1244–1274":"1244–1274","1259":"1259","1258":"1258","1244":"1244","1320":"1320","1274":"1274","about 1274":"noin 1274","Pershore, Worcestershire, England":"Pershore, Worcestershire, England","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Ranska"},"fr":{"1244–about 